ACTRESS Lerato Moloi and her hubby Collen Mashawana have called it quits &ndash; again.Sunday Sun can reveal the on-and-off couple is now officially off.But sources close to the couple say there&rsquo;s no bad blood between them &ndash; even though they have gone their separate ways again.One source said Lerato called it quits after their latest short stint to try and patch things up.At the time, the pair had a traditional wedding in Venda.&ldquo;But that&rsquo;s all over, and Lerato has deleted their photos as a happy couple,&rdquo; said the source.&ldquo;Lerato is fine now. She&rsquo;s trying to pick up the pieces in her life. She&rsquo;s a strong girl and will come through this,&rdquo; added the source.Another close friend claimed the reason for the couple to split was because things didn&rsquo;t work out the way they&rsquo;d planned.&ldquo;After they&rsquo;d given their relationship a second try, they realised love was no longer there,&rdquo; said the friend.Sunday Sun has learnt that the couple is now co-parenting.&ldquo;They are both loving parents and get along well as friends,&rdquo; said the source, who added that the child stays one week with the dad and another with the mum.The source went on to say Collen is a committed dad.&ldquo;Shame, you can&rsquo;t fault him there. He&rsquo;s there for his son and loves him.&rdquo;When called for comment, Collen said he won&rsquo;t talk about his private life in the media.Lerato confirmed they&rsquo;re no longer together and there&rsquo;s no bad blood between them.&ldquo;Look, we&rsquo;re parents to our beautiful son and he&rsquo;s a great dad. There&rsquo;s no drama,&rdquo; she said.